title: For Trade:  M76 Sniper in 8MM want to trade.
postcontent:
I have a one of a kind Zestava M-76. This rifle is double digit serial number, Yes two number serial. Rifle was used by Century arms as their Display rifle and submitted at the 2009 Shot Show. This rifle is immaculate, and comes with all prominence proving the rifle was the display rifle including the red tag placed around trigger guard with the shot show markings and the original owners manual. This rifle is chambered in 8MM mauser and the glass is in fantastic condition. This rifle is milled w/ tapered heavy BBL and threaded for suppressor. Other than looks it has nothing in common with a Dragonuv or PSL and far out classes them. Standard effective range of 850 Meters with decent shooters out to over 1,000 with a trained shooter is normal for this rifle. The barrel is heavy BBL unlike the Dragonuv or PSL and the receiver is milled not stamped cheaply like the Dragunov and PSL with a beautiful smooth finish. 
The scope was designed by the Russians as a passive IR detection scope meaning that the radioactive materials in the scope can detect IR light. The scope was used to look for snipers at night that used IR illuminated night vision without giving away the Russian snipers position as the Russian scope detects IR light and doesn't emit it. This is a Counter Sniper Rifle. Designed as such from the factory. This rifle is currently used by Russia, Croatia, Kosovo, Czech Republic, Romania, Bosnia and North Korea.

One picture is from gunshow review of the exact rifle for sale that was shown in the magazine, Picture was taken at ShotShow, this picture is of the actual rifle being sold that was presented by Century Arms to represent their brand to the public and dealers alike. 

You must have AZ drivers License, CCW or Military I.D a plus but not required. Can provide a Bill of Sale if you wish and show AZ drivers License and Military I.D on my end. I am the original and only owner of this rifle. I have had it for about 5 years, Original owner.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Rare WWI/II Officer's Pistol
postcontent: Becker and Hollander Beholla Pistol. This pistol was bought commercially during WWI and carried as an officer's side arm through the war. The same officer would later carry the pistol through WWII when it was captured and found it's way back stateside via a navy crewman. Unfortunately at some point this pistol was nickel plated, but it is still in fairly nice shape. Part of what makes this pistol unique aside from the fact that only ~45,000 of them were ever made, is that this pistol has it's original factory grips, which were inletted to accept an imperial german crest on each grip. This is the only instance of this I've ever seen. All parts are matching numbers

title: For Sale/Trade:  1962 Belgium Made Browning A5 12ga Magnum
postcontent:
I am looking to get a good quality home defense or tactical shotgun of equal value so I am going to sell/trading this very nice 1962 Belgium made Browning A5 (Auto-5) semiautomatic 12 gauge 3" magnum shotgun. It is a Browning built shotgun and not a Remington built one (Remington also built the A5 for Browning). The serial number starts with 2V which makes it a 1962 Magnum. The barrel has a full choke and is 31.5" long. The recoil on this magnum allows for the shooting of 2.75" shells as well. This shotgun is currently setup to shoot the 2.75" shells and I have the brass rings to increase the recoil pressure for the 3" magnum shells along with the instruction sheet that tells you how to do it (quite simple to do) and I have the original "Duck Plug" for this shotgun. My shotgun comes with an original Browning soft case for a long shotgun. The Barrel bore is like new, the blue is in very good condition and the wood is in good condition. The wood is not cracked anywhere but does have a few small dings with a few places where the hard clear finish has been chipped off. This is a nice old shotgun (50years-old) and it shoots well. These old full choke barrels are not recommended for steel shot but work just fine with lead shot.

I have decided to sell/trade the old shotgun because it's just too long for home defense and I'm not a duck, goose or turkey hunter. It's also a great trap and skeet gun, of which I do not do either. That long barrel with a full choke shoots a very tight pattern for a very long distance so it is a great distance shooter.

I am asking $575 or best reasonable cash offer. I will consider other interesting firearm trades. I would really like a Taurus Judge or a 410ga semi-auto shotgun, .22 magnum rifles and semi-auto pistols. What do you have??? Email, call or text 5zero5-6one0-five two91 with a question or information about something you have to trade. Thanks for looking.
